It could also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it discusses the adoption and choice of co-editing techniques in the real world. Additionally, it could be classified under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as it deals with co-editing interfaces. The paper also involves the study and comparison of different co-editing techniques, which could place it under the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, it could be classified under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category as it discusses the differences between two programming paradigms.
